abstract: At a fund-raiser, Joe Biden fondly recalled that “at least there was some civility’’ when he served in the Senate alongside James Eastland and Herman Talmadge, two segregationists.
snippet: At a fund-raiser, Joe Biden fondly recalled that “at least there was some civility’’ when he served in the Senate alongside James Eastland and Herman Talmadge, two segregationists.
lead_paragraph: Several Democratic presidential candidates sharply criticized Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday for invoking two Southern segregationist senators by name as he defended himself over accusations of being “old-fashioned” and fondly recalled the “civility” of the Senate in the 1970s and 1980s.

abstract: President Trump’s kickoff of his 2020 campaign showed that his portrait of the country is still bleak — and that he needs an opponent beyond Hillary Clinton.
snippet: President Trump’s kickoff of his 2020 campaign showed that his portrait of the country is still bleak — and that he needs an opponent beyond Hillary Clinton.
lead_paragraph: ORLANDO, Fla. — President Trump kicked off his 2020 re-election campaign on Tuesday night in Orlando. Here are eight takeaways.

abstract: To blaze trails, they travel a familiar path.
snippet: To blaze trails, they travel a familiar path.
lead_paragraph: Pete and Chasten Buttigieg celebrated their first wedding anniversary on Sunday. You know this if you’re among Pete’s roughly 1.1 million Twitter followers or Chasten’s 340,000, because they traded sweetly effusive missives, as they frequently do.

headline_main: Pete and Chasten Buttigieg Are a Traditional Wonder

abstract: A bill backed by nearly 60 House Democrats would create a panel to develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.
snippet: A bill backed by nearly 60 House Democrats would create a panel to develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the support of a string of 2020 Democratic presidential candidates, the idea of reparations for African-Americans is gaining traction among Democrats on Capitol Hill, where Speaker Nancy Pelosi backs the establishment of a commission that would develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.

abstract: She surveyed the media landscape and decided that truth was what she said it was.
snippet: She surveyed the media landscape and decided that truth was what she said it was.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Gail, I know you are as gutted as I am by the news that Sarah Huckabee Sanders will step down from her post as White House spokesman. How do you judge her contribution to our nation’s moral health and political well-being?

abstract: Ms. Klobuchar unveiled a list of well over 100 actions, a majority of which she could pursue with executive power.
snippet: Ms. Klobuchar unveiled a list of well over 100 actions, a majority of which she could pursue with executive power.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota on Tuesday unveiled a list of well over 100 actions she would take in her first 100 days as president if she were elected, a show of policymaking force that is intended to provide a crystal-clear view of the early days of her administration.

abstract: Nine candidates for the Democratic nomination spoke at an event in Washington convened by the Poor People’s Campaign, designed to put a spotlight on poverty.
snippet: Nine candidates for the Democratic nomination spoke at an event in Washington convened by the Poor People’s Campaign, designed to put a spotlight on poverty.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. struck a notably different tone than some other Democrats on Monday over how to bring about change in government, defending his approach to working with Republicans during an appearance at a forum where he and eight other presidential candidates shared their views on addressing poverty.

headline_main: 2020 Democrats Address Poverty and Systemic Racism at Presidential Forum
headline_print_headline: At Poverty Forum, Biden Says the South Is in Play

abstract: President Trump withdrew from a 2015 nuclear agreement with Iran and has steadily imposed harsh sanctions on the country. Now Iran is fighting back.
snippet: President Trump withdrew from a 2015 nuclear agreement with Iran and has steadily imposed harsh sanctions on the country. Now Iran is fighting back.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Iran threatened on Monday to accelerate its nuclear program in violation of a 2015 nuclear agreement, moving it closer to the ability to build an atomic weapon — something that President Trump has vowed to prevent.
